## Session startup

1. Load the `harness-kit` skill first, every session.
2. Read **your** state file — resolve it with:
   `echo "state/$(git config user.name | tr "[:upper:] " "[:lower:]-").md"`
   One state file per person at the **root**, not per member: active feature, last verify
   result, blockers, next step. Never write to anyone else's state file.
3. Read the root `CONSTITUTION.md` (shared rules), **plus** `constitutions/<area>.md` for the
   member you are touching (its stack rules). Both are always in context while you work there.
4. Run `{{VERIFY_PRIMARY}}` to confirm a clean baseline before editing.
5. Pick the **one** ready feature (row) from `FEATURES.md` (all its `Depends on` are ✅). Its
   `Area` tells you which member it touches. Set its status to 🔵 and start.

## Verification

Run before claiming any work done. All checks must pass.

```bash
./verify.sh            # every member, in WORKSPACE.md order
./verify.sh <area>     # just one member — faster while iterating
```

`verify.sh` prints a final `HARNESS_VERIFY: PASS` / `FAIL` line — that line is your evidence.
Only checks each member actually has are listed. Do not invent lint/test/e2e steps.

## Definition of done

A feature (row) is `✅` only when: its `Done when` criteria are met, `verify.sh` passes for its
Area, evidence (naming that Area) is recorded in its `FEATURES.md` sub-table, and your state
file is updated with the next step. A cross-area story is done when all its rows are ✅.

## Session handoff

- Keep your state file current in real time — flip status the moment it changes.
- After every edit, append to its `Changes` table (file · what · why).
- Before ending: run verify, record the result, leave your state file resumable on its own.
- When a feature closes, rotate its detail to `archive/features/<id>.md` and replace its
  Evidence cell with a link. Write the archive file *first*, then remove the detail.

